02:30.360 --> 02:44.020
Russo, and there was a lot of Burroughs, Mars and Venus and Pellucidar and
those, and also in Blue Book Magazine. By 1930 we had about seven magazines. We

02:44.020 --> 02:54.700
had the amazing quarterlies in addition to the monthlies, and Science Wonder had
come along, which also had a quarterly publication, and Air Wonder, and then

02:54.700 --> 03:04.860
there was Astounding Stories of Super Science started up, which is still going
today under the modified title Analog Science Fiction. And that original amazing

03:04.860 --> 03:19.820
from April 1926 is still being published and in my collection. By 1929 a rather
mundane mother began, had begun to be somewhat worried about my collecting

03:19.820 --> 03:29.600
instincts. She had counted my magazines, said, Son, do you realize you have 27
of these magazines? Now if you continue at that rate till you were a grown man,

03:29.740 --> 03:40.480
why, you might have 100 magazines. Well, my dear mother lived till nearly 94 and
was in my own home at the end of her life. The home was now four stories, 17

03:40.480 --> 03:50.580
rooms, three garages in which you couldn't park a toothpick, because we
eliminated the cars from them and put in shelves, and that is totaled with the

03:50.580 --> 03:57.980
Science Fiction collections. As a matter of fact, whenever I see a garage sale
nowadays, I buy another garage. I have two extra garages that are filling up

03:57.980 --> 04:09.180
around Los Angeles. So the collection has grown from that one single magazine
back in October 1926. Here I am on the verge of my 55th anniversary in the

04:09.180 --> 04:23.760
field. Now there are 300,000 magazines and books and manuscripts and props from
movies and artwork and stills. It's just, I stop at nothing, I even try to get

04:23.760 --> 04:25.480
space stamps from all over the world.

